@startuml c4-jotp-08b-mailbox-operations
title JOTP - Mailbox Operations (LinkedTransferQueue)

object "Mailbox\n(LinkedTransferQueue<M>)" as Mailbox {
  note
    Lock-free MPMC queue
    Wait-free enqueue
    Fair dequeue ordering
  end note
}

object "Message Queue\n(Linked Nodes)" as Queue {
  object "Node: Msg1" as N1
  object "Node: Msg2" as N2
  object "Node: Msg3" as N3
  object "Node: Msg4" as N4
}

object "Enqueue\nOperations" as Enqueue {
  note
    put(msg) - non-blocking
    Never waits
    Atomic CAS loop
  end note
}

object "Dequeue\nOperations" as Dequeue {
  note
    take() - blocking
    Waits if empty
    Fair FIFO order

    poll(timeout) - timed
    Returns after timeout
  end note
}

object "Multiple\nSenders" as Senders {
  note
    Process A.send()
    Process B.send()
    Timer delivery
    All concurrent
  end note
}

object "Single\nReceiver" as Receiver {
  note
    Process P.handler
    Dequeues messages
    Processes FIFO
    Updates state
  end note
}

Mailbox *-- Queue: stores

Queue: Head -> N1
Queue: N1 -> N2
Queue: N2 -> N3
Queue: N3 -> N4
Queue: N4 -> Tail

Enqueue --> Mailbox: append nodes
Dequeue --> Mailbox: remove from head

Senders --> Enqueue: concurrent\nadd to queue
Receiver --> Dequeue: exclusive\nremove from queue

note bottom of Mailbox
  put() is wait-free - always completes in bounded time
  take() is blocking - waits on internal condition variable
  No explicit locking - atomic operations only
  Scales well - MPMC without contention
end note

SHOW_LEGEND()

@enduml
